===Overview===
[[File:British_Flag.png|thumb|left]]
The '''British Empire''' was a [[Earth|worldwide system]] of dependencies under the sovereignty of the crown of [[Great Britain]]. It began in [[England]] followed by the conquest over the rest of the British Isles. The empire's capital was in [[London (England)|London]]. At its height in the late 19th and early 20th centuries it was the largest empire in history and covered about a quarter of the world’s land surface with territory on every continent. Trade ties with nations outside of its sovereignty reinforced its global dominance.

===16th Century===
[[John Dee (Earth-616)|John Dee]], mathematician, astrologer and personal Dark Wizard to [[Elizabeth Tudor (Earth-616)|Queen Elizabeth I]] created the [[Empire Stone]]. This magic stone allowed a small island off the coast of [[Europe]] to become the leader of the largest empire in history of the world.{{r|Union Vol 1 4}}

England made its initial attempts for overseas settlements in the 16th century with the earliest settlements formed under the enterprise of companies, often encouraged by the crown. These areas of influence were scattered in [[North America]] and [[Asia|East Asia]].

In 1591, the first [[England|English colony]] was settled on [[Roanoke Island]]. It did not survive as it was attacked by a vampire who turned all the 121 settlers into vampires leaving only one message carved into a tree "Croatoan".{{r|Marvel Comics Presents Vol 1 63}}

====17th Century====
In 1617 AD, the Mughal Emperor of [[India]] gave the [[British East India Company (Earth-616)|British East India Company]] permission to trade. They became a superpower in the region with rulers becoming dependent on the company's financial and military backing.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[India]]'s entry}}

Shipping and trade were the main ways Britain exercised control in the 17th century. Colonies were regarded as a source of raw materials. During this century sugar and tobacco plantations were developed in the [[Caribbean]] and [[North America]]. These expedition were lead by [[Francis Drake (Earth-616)|Sir Francis Drake]] on one such expedition the ships surgeon was injured by the natives becoming the immortal creature known as [[Bloodscream (Earth-616)|Bloodscream]].{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 #78}}

The [[Pilgrims (Earth-616)|Pilgrims]] a group of English settlers who were fleeing the volatile political environment in [[England]] travelled aboard the [[Mayflower]], from [[Plymouth]] to the [[America|New World]]. At least one member of the [[Clan Akkaba (Earth-616)|Clan Akkaba]] was on board the ship.{{r|X-Men: Apocalypse vs. Dracula #1}}

Another Pilgrim ship the [[Pandora]] was across the [[Atlantic Ocean]] to restart in the New World. One day their ship was swept in a whirlpool that was also a portal into the [[Negative Zone]]. They have spent the centuries fighting [[Annihilus (Earth-616)|Annihilus]] whom they view as the literal Biblical [[Devil]].{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 3 41}}

In 1649, [[Oliver Cromwell (Earth-616)|Oliver Cromwell]] led the [[British Army (Earth-616)|English Army]] into [[Ireland]], forcing them under British rule. This lasted all the way until the 20th Century.{{r|Amazing High Adventure #1}}

The [[Clan Akkaba (Earth-616)|Clan Akkaba]] settled in London using the growing empire to influence the world and their mission of safeguarding the legacies and mantras of their [[En Sabah Nur (Earth-616)|lord and ancestor]]. They even had a member aboard the Mayflower's voyage to the New World.{{r|X-Men: Apocalypse vs. Dracula #1}}

The African slave trade provided cheap labor for those plantations and led to the development of a wider sphere of influence in [[Africa]].{{Citation}}

===18th Century===
In the 18th century, British military and naval power was the engine driving colonial expansion.

Western trade began and became very favorable at first for China with porcelain and tea in demand, while they wanted very little form westerners, however the British Empire found a market importing [[Indian]] cotton and opium. The latter was banned by imperial decree.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[China]]'s entry}}

The [[Hellfire Club (Earth-616)|Hellfire Club]] began in London as a social club for the British social elite and wealthy in the 1760's as a way to provide its members with pleasures that often defied the moral standards of the time and to allow members to consolidate their influence over British economic and political matters.{{r|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Vol 1 5}}

A war between the Britain and France caused great conflict in the world and the territories. It was at this time the [[American Revolutionary War]] began, and they lost the 13 colonies that formed their own independent nation, the [[United States of America]].{{r|Captain America Vol 1 194}}{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 4 10}} 

In 1770 AD, [[James Cook (Earth-616)|Captain James Cook]] charts the east coast of [[Australia]] in his ship HM Endeavour. Cook claims it as part of the British Empire and names eastern Australia "[[New South Wales]]".{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Australia]]'s entry}}

===19th Century===
In the 19th century, the Empire was at its peak ruling over half the planet. The Empire developed a unified system of colonial governance. In 1807, slavery was abolished throughout the empire.

The Empire went to war with France beginning the [[Napoleonic Wars]] in 1803.{{r|Mystic Vol 1 44}} Britain defeated [[Napoléon Bonaparte (Earth-616)|Napoléon Bonaparte]] and his armies at [[Waterloo]] in 1815 and took many of their colonies in the process.{{r|Amazing High Adventure Vol 1 4}}

It was during this time which became known as the [[War of 1812]], a conflict between the USA and the British Empire. It was during this time that the [[White House]] was burnt down.{{r|Invincible Iron Man Vol 1 506}}{{r|Marvel Tales Vol 1 156}}

In the 19th century, the British arrived settling a colony that would later become the nation of Australia.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Australia]]'s entry}}

====[[First Opium War]]====
In 1839, China tried to stop the opium trade and commissioner [[Lin Zexu (Earth-616)|Lin Zexu]] detained all foreigners in [[Guangzhou]] and destroyed 2000 chests of opium. In retaliation, Britain declared war, defeating China with 3 years. This lead to the concession of [[Hong Kong]] being signed over to them for the next 150 years.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[China]]'s entry}}

====British Raj====
In 1850 AD, while many native princes nominally ruled, the true power was with the company whole controlled most of India. The aftermath of the 1857 AD Indian Rebellion saw the British government dissolve the Company, administering the regions directly and with local leaders.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[India]]'s entry}}

====Crimean War ====
The war lasted from 1854 to 1856 was fought by an alliance of the Britain, [[French Empire]], [[Ottoman Empire]] and [[Sardinia]] against [[Russian Empire]]. During the war a soldier tired of fighting witnesses the "Charge of the Light Brigade" which reinvigorates his fighting spirit.{{r|Battleground Vol 1 15}} [[Walter Destine (Earth-616)|Walter Destine]] served in the [[British Army (Earth-616)|British Army]] during the war.{{r|ClanDestine Vol 2 5}}

In 1867, an Indian man fed up with British rule summoned the powers of the [[Daevas|Hindu Gods]] to fight back against the [[British East India Company (Earth-616)|British East India Company]]. His victory was almost certain but his arrogance got the best of him and he was killed by the British soldiers.{{r|Amazing High Adventure Vol 1 5}}

====[[Second Opium War]]====
In 1860, the British and the French allied together to fight the [[China|Chinese]] during the the Second Opium War. They faced the [[Bei Bang-Wen (Earth-616)|Iron Fist]] at the Forts of Taku. Although a great warrior, he and his army lost, were taken prisoner, and forced into hard labor, and then the power of the [[Iron Fist]] left him.{{r|Immortal Iron Fist Vol 1 #3}}

They then began colonizing [[New Zealand]] and the rest of the [[Pacific]] region.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[New Zealand]]'s entry}}

In 1882, [[Egypt]] became a British protectorate, in doing so they took control of the [[Suez Canal]], a vital trading hub.{{r|Marvel Atlas #2|; [[Egypt]]'s entry}}

====[[Boxer Rebellion]]====
In 1899 AD, colonial powers intervened in the [[Boxer Rebellion]] in China.{{r|Semper Fi #4}}

===20th Century===
The 20th century was the beginning of the end of the British Empire. In 1907, self-governing colonies including [[Canada]], [[Australia]], and [[South Africa]] were granted the status of dominions.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Australia]]'s entry}}

====[[World War I]]====
In 1914, they went to war with [[Germany]] which became known as [[World War I]]. This lasted until 1918. After the war Canada, Australia, and South Africa became independent nations.{{Citation}}

====[[World War II]]==== 
In 1939, Germany invaded [[Poland]] and allies of Great Britain beginning [[World War II]].{{Citation}}

===End of the Empire===
In 1947, India gains it's independence and is split into the free states of India, Pakistan, and Bangladesh.{{r|Marvel Atlas #2|; [[India]]'s entry}} 

The final British colony, [[Hong Kong]], was returned to Chinese sovereignty in 1997.{{Citation}}
